# Welcome!

This is your first blog post. Congratulations on setting up your new Jekyll site with the **{{THEME_DISPLAY_NAME}}**!

## Getting Started

Here are some things you can do next:

1. **Customize your site** - Edit `_config.yml` to set your site title, description, and other settings
2. **Add more posts** - Create new files in `pages/_posts/` using the format `YYYY-MM-DD-title.md`
3. **Create documentation** - Add pages to `pages/_docs/` for your documentation
4. **Personalize the theme** - Modify styles in `_sass/custom.scss`

## Writing Posts

Posts are written in Markdown with YAML front matter. Here's an example structure:

```yaml
---
layout: journals
title: "Your Post Title"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
categories: [Category]
tags: [tag1, tag2]
---

Your content here...
```

## Features Available

- **Code highlighting** - Use fenced code blocks with language identifiers
- **Mermaid diagrams** - Create flowcharts and diagrams
- **Bootstrap components** - Full access to Bootstrap 5.3 classes
- **Dark mode** - Automatic theme switching based on user preference

